售，我们就必须做出这一调整。” Ascendant将为下岗工人提供遣散费，并帮助他们在其他地方找到工作。剩下的团队成员暂时会继续支持游戏。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="c3a601bafa9c4affa4a2dc0a79b94245"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="zxx" dir="ltr"> <a href="https://t.co/gftU3XlbFZ">pic.twitter.com/gftU3XlbFZ</a></p> — 布雷特·罗宾斯 (@BretRobbins) <a href="https://twitter.com/BretRobbins/status/1702397324755083719?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 9 月 14 日</a></blockquote></div><p><em>Immortals of Aveum</em>是 Ascendant 的第一款游戏，Ascendant 是一家独立工作室，由经验丰富的开发人员掌舵。然而，发行商 EA 可能并没有在游戏的发行日期上给游戏带来任何好处。</p><p>在<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/eas-immortals-of-aveum-is-delayed-until-august-22nd-180133135.html"><ins>游戏延迟</ins></a>一个月至 8 月 22 日之后， <em>《Immortals of Aveum》</em>与<em>《博德之门 III》、</em> <em>《装甲核心 VI》</em>和<em>《Starfield》</em>大约在同一时间上市。考虑到我们即将<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/assassins-creed-mirage-preview-a-throwback-in-the-best-of-ways-120018919.html"><ins>进入</ins></a>数年来<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/call-of-duty-modern-warfare-iii-will-use-ai-to-clamp-down-on-toxic-voice-chats-160027704.html"><ins>主要游戏发布</ins></a><a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/alan-wake-ii-delayed-by-10-days-will-arrive-on-october-27th-150033546.html"><ins>最繁忙的时期</ins></a>之一，将<em>《Aveum 不朽》</em>再推迟几周可能也无济于事。</p><p>有报道称<em>《Immortals of Aveum》</em> （主要<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.metacritic.com/game/immortals-of-aveum/critic-reviews/?platform=pc"><ins>获得中等评价</ins></a>）销量不佳，Steam 上的低玩家数量表明情况确实如此。根据<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://steamdb.info/app/2009100/charts/"><ins>SteamDB 的数据</ins></a>，该平台上的峰值玩家数量仅为 751 人。仅 Steam 上<em>《Starfield</em> 》的峰值玩家数量就<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://steamdb.info/app/1716740/charts/"><ins>超过了这个数字的 440 倍</ins></a>。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/immortals-of-aveum-developer-ascendant-studios-lays-off-almost-half-its-staff-161523899.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/immortals-of-aveum-developer-ascendant-studios-lays-off-almost-half-its-staff-161523899.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> a2b49533-44f1-47a0-b445-8d576d7587ef</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 15 Sep 2023 16:15:23 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694793749</ingested><modified> 2023-09-15T16:02:33+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/46d62d20-0f91-11ee-97e5-ce40e3c1681a" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/46d62d20-0f91-11ee-97e5-ce40e3c1681a" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Ascendant Studios/EA]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A character wearing a cape and surrounded by a circular blue rune holds up a glowing, gloved fist in Immortals of Aveum.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Immortals of Aveum]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Apple isn’t perfect on environment isues, but it’s depressingly ahead of its peers]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>在 iPhone 15 发布会上，苹果发布了一张草图，其中首席执行官蒂姆·库克 (Tim Cook) 和副总裁丽莎·杰克逊 (Lisa Jackson) 与奥克塔维亚·斯宾塞 (Octavia Spencer) 的《Mother Nature》一起吹嘘了公司的环保目标。这一举措旨在帮助加强<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-watch-series-9-can-handle-siri-requests-without-your-iphone-171920001.html">Apple Watch 9 的营销，</a>其中某些版本以碳中和的形式出售。这是第一款带有该品牌的产品，但随着苹果公司努力实现到 2030 年实现完全碳中和的目标，其他产品也会效仿。然而，正是在这次活动之后，我想知道这其中有多少是苹果公司沾沾自喜地祝贺自己所做的工作。这是应该做的。</p><p>移动领域有很多公司，但并不是所有公司都像苹果一样擅长为面包和黄油做歌舞。因此，我想我应该阅读去年所有公司的可持续发展报告，看看这种咆哮是否值得戳破。但是，尽管我们可能很想嘲笑苹果公司的自鸣得意，但事实证明，没有一家大型制造商能够接近夺取这一光环。事实上，我度过了相当痛苦的几天，即使是现在，我也了解到该领域的一些大人物所做的事情是多么的少。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Apple;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=4130e2f0-a14f-4c5e-bdab-cd52ac7d8e79&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Apple&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hcHBsZS5jb20vdWsvZW52aXJvbm1lbnQvcGRmL0dCRU5fQXBwbGVfRW52aXJvbm1lbnRhbF9Qcm9ncmVzc19SZXBvcnRfMjAyMy5wZGYiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6Ijk3ZjU4MGU1LTZjOWMtNGQ1Mi04MjQ3LTJmYTRiMzhlYjdhOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAVL0s_5gO_xhWD1YOm2iewBo5Bi1XjfrLuiT-qF6G5Wg&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apple.com%2Fuk%2Fenvironment%2Fpdf%2FGBEN_Apple_Environmental_Progress_Report_2023.pdf" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.apple.com/uk/environment/pdf/GBEN_Apple_Environmental_Progress_Report_2023.pdf">苹果的</a>目标非常激进，一些国内竞争对手也与之相匹配，尽管它们的硬件业务要小得多。 Facebook 所有者<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://sustainability.fb.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Meta-2023-Path-to-Net-Zero.pdf">Meta</a>主要是一家服务公司，其在 2020 年的全球业务中实现了净零，并希望到 2030 年在其整个价值链上实现净零。 <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Microsoft;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=67071605-d4df-494e-8d9c-c9c236b8bb38&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Microsoft&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5taWNyb3NvZnQuY29tL2VuLXVzL2NvcnBvcmF0ZS1yZXNwb25zaWJpbGl0eS9zdXN0YWluYWJpbGl0eS9yZXBvcnQiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6Ijk3ZjU4MGU1LTZjOWMtNGQ1Mi04MjQ3LTJmYTRiMzhlYjdhOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAR6TsBziPfAAv81c8yuklRTh4aCDoYu0Bp-iR1eI_Wpz&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.microsoft.com%2Fen-us%2Fcorporate-responsibility%2Fsustainability%2Freport" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/corporate-responsibility/sustainability/report">微软的</a>目标甚至更大，因为它承诺成为到 2030 年成为<em>碳负</em>公司。与此同时，<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://sustainability.google/operating-sustainably/">谷歌</a>希望到 2030 年在其运营的每个地方实现无碳能源，但它相信在同一期限之前它只能将排放量减少一半。 <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://sustainability.aboutamazon.com/2022-sustainability-report.pdf">亚马逊</a>在解决可持续发展问题上一直是最引人注目的落后者，它承诺到 2040 年实现净零排放。</p><p>在我们深入研究之前，值得注意的是，不能保证不同公司的报告之间的一致性，而且数据并不总是全面的。我们不能忽视苹果与其最大的移动竞争对手三星之间巨大的财务差距。同样，三星与市场中低端厂商之间的财务差距也很明显，关心环境也需要花钱。但即便如此，这些公司做出的软弱承诺甚至没有看上去那么好。 （今年早些时候， <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://newclimate.org/resources/publications/corporate-climate-responsibility-monitor-2023">新气候研究所</a>在透明度和完整性方面给三星的<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://newclimate.org/news/reaction-samsung-electronics-joining-re100-and-committing-to-net-zero-by-2050">气候承诺</a>打了不及格的分数，并指出其雄心勃勃。）</p><p>我不会用<em>每一项</em>统计数据让你感到厌烦——尽管我确实可以——但苹果公司几乎领先于所有人。以电子垃圾为例，苹果公司声称将把超过 40,000 吨的废弃电子产品直接进行回收而不是填埋。它没有详细说明从中恢复了多少，但它仍然是一个相当引人注目的数字。 <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Samsung Electronics;elmt:;cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=f85e63cd-e13c-4f9d-991c-9fbaadede3ac&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Samsung+Electronics&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5zYW1zdW5nLmNvbS9nbG9iYWwvc3VzdGFpbmFiaWxpdHkvbWVkaWEvcGRmL1NhbXN1bmdfRWxlY3Ryb25pY3NfU3VzdGFpbmFiaWxpdHlfUmVwb3J0XzIwMjNfRU5HLnBkZiIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiOTdmNTgwZTUtNmM5Yy00ZDUyLTgyNDctMmZhNGIzOGViN2E4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAUNr6winr9bsPVgfAjK1TNZ1aR4ylRNARnbK1rjc3VBj&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.samsung.com%2Fglobal%2Fsustainability%2Fmedia%2Fpdf%2FSamsung_Electronics_Sustainability_Report_2023_ENG.pdf" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.samsung.com/global/sustainability/media/pdf/Samsung_Electronics_Sustainability_Report_2023_ENG.pdf">三星</a>似乎收集了大约四分之一的数据，根据我的古怪计算，大约回收了 80% 的数据以供重复使用。</p><p>与此同时，2022 年第三大手机厂商<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://xiaomi.gcs-web.com/system/files-encrypted/nasdaq_kms/assets/2023/04/26/10-13-04/2022%20ESG%20Report_ENG.pdf">小米</a>自豪地报告称，该公司已将 4,500 吨电子垃圾投入回收。与世界第四的<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5vcHBvLmNvbS9lbi9vcHBvLXN1c3RhaW5hYmlsaXR5LyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiOTdmNTgwZTUtNmM5Yy00ZDUyLTgyNDctMmZhNGIzOGViN2E4In0&amp;signature=AQAAAQtlYFSd0q8JYPM0B56QP9O77nVcNnqICBwdSspcv4YE&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oppo.com%2Fen%2Foppo-sustainability%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.oppo.com/en/oppo-sustainability/">Oppo</a>相比，这个数字看起来不错，后者仅用 195 吨就做到了这一点。 TECNO 和 Infinix 的母公司<a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://static.sse.com.cn/disclosure/listedinfo/announcement/c/new/2023-04-26/688036_20230426_ME64.pdf">Transsion</a>仅承诺开展回收计划。值得记住的是， <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://weee-forum.org/ws_news/of-16-billion-mobile-phones-possessed-worldwide-5-3-billion-will-become-waste-in-2022/">WEEE 论坛</a>预测，到 2022 年，多达 53 亿台移动设备将不再使用，基本上变成垃圾。</p><p>令我惊讶的是，苹果公司甚至愿意提及供应商工厂的排放量，因为它外包了制造。很容易将其肮脏的排放物洗到其他公司的资产负债表上，并单独指出其公司用途。相反，它收到了许多供应商的承诺，承诺使用 100% 可再生能源。苹果表示，其供应链目前拥有 13.7GW 的可再生能源，不久的将来还会有 6.3GW 的可再生能源。与此同时，三星表示，计划到 2027 年在其所有业务场所实现 100% 可再生能源，并且已经使用绿色电力满足 31% 的需求。小米似乎并未承诺坚定地向可再生能源转型，而 Oppo 则认为，其碳排放峰值要到<em>明年</em>才能达到。</p><p>如果说苹果在某一方面仍然落后于行业其他公司，至少目前如此，那么它正在修复中。至少在我们知道最终用户更换 iPhone 15 上的通用组件有多么容易之前，苹果仍然和其他公司一样糟糕。其自助维修平台仍然复杂得令人沮丧，而且基本维修费用仍然过高。 （或者只是拒绝维修设备作为让买家更换设备的先兆。）三星在自己的报告中对可维修性进行了相当大的讨论，并以 Galaxy S23 为例。值得注意的是，iFixit 的专家对 S23 的<a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.ifixit.com/News/72731/samsung-galaxy-s23-introduces-killer-feature-from-the-iphone-4#:~:text=The%20S21%20just%20managed%20to,adhesive%E2%80%94nearly%20invisible%20from%20here.">可修复性评分为 4/10</a> ，因为虽然电池是可更换的，但它也是<em>粘</em>在适当位置的。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/55c211c0-53d7-11ee-adbf-8422dd5a5e19" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/55c211c0-53d7-11ee-adbf-8422dd5a5e19" style="height:4094px;width:6141px;" alt="2023 年 9 月 12 日，在加利福尼亚州库比蒂诺 Apple Park 举行的发布会上，Apple Watch Series 9 型号与其他新产品一起展示。（摄影：Nic Coury / 法新社）（摄影：NIC COURY / 法新社，盖蒂图片社）" data-uuid="c2ab3f52-f261-3958-9ca8-269323ab62c1"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> NIC COURY 来自 Getty Images</div></figure><p>就 Apple 而言，它对 Watch Series 9 的分类做出了一些相当大胆的声明。该公司表示，该设备由 30% 的回收或可再生材料制成，包括 100% 回收铝制成的外壳。这款手表是在使用 100% 可再生能源的工厂生产的，其中至少一半是通过海运而非空运运输的。该公司补充说，它不仅支付其制造设备的清洁能源费用，而且还投资于与用户充电时可能消耗的电力相同的发电量。</p><p>该公司表示，根据自己的指标，该腕表的制造排放基准为 36.7 公斤。从此，它成功地降低了能源排放成本，并减少了材料和工艺排放。就 Apple 而言，Series 9 仅向大气排放 8.1 公斤，然后用碳信用额抵消。</p><p>该公司在其<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Apple;elmt:;cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=4130e2f0-a14f-4c5e-bdab-cd52ac7d8e79&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Apple&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hcHBsZS5jb20vZW52aXJvbm1lbnQvcGRmL3Byb2R1Y3RzL3dhdGNoL0NhcmJvbl9OZXV0cmFsX0FwcGxlX1dhdGNoX1Nlcmllc185X1BFUl9TZXB0MjAyMy5wZGYiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6Ijk3ZjU4MGU1LTZjOWMtNGQ1Mi04MjQ3LTJmYTRiMzhlYjdhOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAQGbB0paontA7BaLmO0d4ybRtXsJvHX23a9J1EB_KjSA&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apple.com%2Fenvironment%2Fpdf%2Fproducts%2Fwatch%2FCarbon_Neutral_Apple_Watch_Series_9_PER_Sept2023.pdf" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.apple.com/environment/pdf/products/watch/Carbon_Neutral_Apple_Watch_Series_9_PER_Sept2023.pdf">材料</a>中引用了苹果公司创立的<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Apple;elmt:;cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=4130e2f0-a14f-4c5e-bdab-cd52ac7d8e79&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Apple&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hcHBsZS5jb20vdWsvbmV3c3Jvb20vMjAyMy8wNC9hcHBsZS1leHBhbmRzLWlubm92YXRpdmUtcmVzdG9yZS1mdW5kLWZvci1jYXJib24tcmVtb3ZhbC8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6Ijk3ZjU4MGU1LTZjOWMtNGQ1Mi04MjQ3LTJmYTRiMzhlYjdhOCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAcs-7XmAJ_UUhQVXrZahvj0ttwhUtNmxcdY9kCzq-tPQ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apple.com%2Fuk%2Fnewsroom%2F2023%2F04%2Fapple-expands-innovative-restore-fund-for-carbon-removal%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.apple.com/uk/newsroom/2023/04/apple-expands-innovative-restore-fund-for-carbon-removal/">恢复基金</a>项目，该项目投资于“高质量、基于自然的碳清除项目”。恢复基金与保护国际组织、高盛和汇丰银行合作运营，但它并不完全是慈善性质的。高盛<a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.goldmansachs.com/careers/possibilities/apple-carbon/">自己的网站</a>将该基金描述为盈利性基金，提供“来自收获活动和财产出售的未来潜在财务回报”。</p><p>对抵消采购持怀疑态度是值得的，特别是因为该行业并不像您希望的那样干净。今年早些时候， <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/jan/18/revealed-forest-carbon-offsets-biggest-provider-worthless-verra-aoe"><em>《卫报》</em></a>发表了对 Verra 的调查，该机构负责验证各种大公司运营的碳抵消计划。研究发现，公司为减少排放而购买的许多信用额根本没有转化为现实世界的行动。报告显示，在购买的 9490 万碳信用额中，实际减排量仅为 550 万 MTCO2e（公吨二氧化碳当量）。维拉对这些发现提出异议。</p><p>值得重申的是，苹果公司在这方面处于某种特权地位，因为它手头有数量惊人的现金。它可以利用这种力量在可再生能源领域进行引人注目的投资，而这是其竞争对手可能没有的。但它的财富也成为了进步批评者的目标，其中包括<a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://populationmatters.org/iphone-upgrades-environmental-insanity-says-charity/"><em>人口问题</em></a>等机构，他们指出，仅该公司的年度营销预算就可以为联合国 46 个最不发达国家带来清洁水。</p><p>但是，从总体来看，移动设备领域只有一家公司可以在绿色赌注中远远超过苹果： <a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://www.fairphone.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Fairphone-Impact-Report-2022.pdf">Fairphone</a> 。它仍然是一个相对小众的参与者，但已将打造对道德和环境负责的设备作为其指导使命。最大的问题是，所有最大的参与者需要多长时间才能赶上这家小公司目前的水平。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/apple-isnt-perfect-on-environment-isues-but-its-depressingly-ahead-of-its-peers-160051378.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/apple-isnt-perfect-on-environment-isues-but-its-depressingly-ahead-of-its-peers-160051378.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 97f580e5-6c9c-4d52-8247-2fa4b38eb7a8</guid><dc:creator>丹尼尔·库珀</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 15 Sep 2023 16:00:51 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694792883</ingested><modified> 2023-09-15T15:48:08+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Personal Investing Ideas & Strategies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Environment]]></category><category><![CDATA[Nature & Environment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Daniel Cooper]]></category><media:content height="3651" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/94ec1d00-53d7-11ee-8be9-ef70ef0588d5" width="5476"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3651" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/94ec1d00-53d7-11ee-8be9-ef70ef0588d5" width="5476"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NIC COURY via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[People walk through the Steve Jobs Theater prior to an event at the Apple Park campus in Cupertino, California, on September 12, 2023. The new Apple iPhone 15, with EU ordered USB-C charger, is expected to be announced, amongst other new products, during a launch event on September 12. (Photo by Nic Coury / AFP) (Photo by NIC COURY/AFP via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[US-TECH-APPLE-IPHONE]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The first-ever party-based RPG is getting a serious facelift]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>早在 1981 年，当<em>《Wizardry》</em>在 Apple II 上发布时，它就席卷了整个游戏界，而现在它又卷土重来，吸引了新一代的 RPG 粉丝。开发商 Digital Eclipse 正在重新制作这款回合制游戏，现在的名称为<em>《Wizardry: Proving Grounds of the Mad Overlord》</em> 。</p><p>该重制版是 1981 年 RPG 的现代化版本，它构建在原始 Apple II 代码之上，因此您可以轻松地从老式界面切换到全新的图形，类似于<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2014-08-22-halo-2-anniversary.html"><ins>“光环 2：周年纪念日” ”版本</ins></a>处理的事情，或者是<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hk55TwWYTFg"><ins>刚刚宣布的</ins><em><ins>古墓丽影</ins></em><ins>重制版</ins></a><ins></ins>适用于任天堂 Switch。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>现代视觉效果很不错，但<em>《Wizardry》</em>已有 40 多年的历史，因此游戏玩法可能有点过时。为此，开发商承诺进行一系列生活质量改进，包括改进的队伍管理系统、新的施法选项和导航工具，以及其他小的升级。 </p><div id="839a11f542314dd398c3c4689c59d359"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/n_ftSnfc4oE?si=1B7HjTaSdAkZDQ9p" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div><p> <em>《Wizardry》</em>通常被认为是第一个在电脑或游戏机上发布的团队角色扮演游戏，并启发了无数现代系列游戏， <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.gamedeveloper.com/design/the-unlikely-origin-story-of-jrpgs">包括《最终幻想》和《勇者斗恶龙》。</a>它不是第一个为电脑增光添彩的<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.mobygames.com/game/3986/oubliette/"><ins>龙与地下城风格的角色扮演游戏</ins></a>，但它确实发明了许多至今仍活跃在日式角色扮演游戏中的机制。它在 Apple II 上推出后立即大受欢迎，并被移植到许多其他系统，包括 Mac、C64 甚至 NES 和 Game Boy Color。</p><p>这并不是 Digital Eclipse 第一次翻拍牛仔竞技表演。该团队曾制作过许多复古作品，包括<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/atari-50-the-anniversary-collection-announced-161306163.html"><em>《Atari 50》</em></a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/teenage-mutant-ninja-turtles-cowabunga-collection-release-date-140016805.html"><em>《忍者神龟：Cowabunga Collection》</em></a>等。</p><p> <em>《巫师：疯狂霸主的试验场》</em>现已通过 Steam 和 GOG 推出抢先体验版本。该游戏售价 30 美元，但开发者表示，随着正式发布的临近​​，价格可能会上涨。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/the-first-ever-party-based-rpg-is-getting-a-serious-facelift-153737569.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-first-ever-party-based-rpg-is-getting-a-serious-facelift-153737569.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 015e44b7-5833-4e57-a535-cfef972ff92d</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 15 Sep 2023 15:37:37 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694792258</ingested><modified> 2023-09-15T15:37:41+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="1370" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/c6b5d560-53dc-11ee-af68-ce634bbb519e" width="2468"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1370" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/c6b5d560-53dc-11ee-af68-ce634bbb519e" width="2468"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Digital Eclipse ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Title screen from the new Wizardry.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Wizardry ]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best iPhone cases for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>这个世界上有两种人：一种是裸着 iPhone 的人，另一种是拆开包装后就把手机塞进保护套里的人。如果您刚刚购买了一部新 iPhone，属于后一类，并且正在寻求一定程度的保护，那么您有大量的选择需要考虑。在亚马逊上研究你从未听说过的公司的热门案例，很容易掉进兔子洞。您可能会想要购买最便宜的手机壳，或者带有最可爱图案或卡夹的手机壳，但它们可能不是满足您需求的最佳 iPhone 手机壳，尤其是当您正在寻找 MagSafe 手机壳时。我们测试了多种适用于各种 iPhone 型号的最新手机壳、保护套和保护膜，以选出真正物有所值的首选产品。</p><h2> Spigen 超混合 Magfit </h2><p><core-commerce id="f5b1764bac0f4c9891734ea5abd76282" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>如果您想要一款价格实惠的基本型保护套， <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWXXzLXDP3NWu4yUddNUFfEOTC0JLYp3_uQZtsXH8akF&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fstores%2FSpigen%2Fpage%2F1B6B4933-0D21-4FF4-AB37-F74CD4F5CB1C%3Fref_%3Dast_bln">Spigen</a>可以满足您的需求。该公司的<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1NwaWdlbi1IeWJyaWQtTWFnRml0LURlc2lnbmVkLWlQaG9uZS9kcC9CMEM1UzlQMTdXP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWJ6LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJjMjVjMDc0Ny1mODdkLTRjOGYtYTM4Mi00Yjc2ZjkxYjIyNjUifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAVLmNZ2QovBtTxwDizfGiViKrCv8MQwrMfhhJH2efnTl&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSpigen-Hybrid-MagFit-Designed-iPhone%2Fdp%2FB0C5S9P17W" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/Spigen-Hybrid-MagFit-Designed-iPhone/dp/B0C5S9P17W?ref_=ast_sto_dp&amp;th=1&amp;psc=1">Ultra Hybrid MagFit 透明保护壳</a>展示了 iPhone 的颜色，我们喜欢其凸起的边框，可以保护后置摄像头。这些保护壳的侧面还设有战术按钮，让您无需看手机即可轻松摸索并调节手机音量。聚碳酸酯保护壳整体纤薄，可以轻松固定在 iPhone 上，而不会增加太多体积，而且它还兼容 MagSafe，因此无线充电非常方便。此外，Ultra Hybrid 保护壳是我们尝试过的最安全的保护壳之一，以至于当我们需要测试新的手机保护壳时，几乎很难将 iPhone 取出。虽然它们的售价通常约为 45 美元，但您经常会发现它们的售价为 25 至 30 美元。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2>聪明的狮鹫</h2><p><core-commerce id="469a803376754335b2d9bd4d89d2e5fe" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>我们过去推荐过<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUobfKshMNVnwyZ9Kbq5C1xLSsaWS0LF4UABl_5-h6FI&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fstores%2FSmartish-PhoneCasesandStuff%2Fpage%2F6B17F407-9983-45D5-A90E-6B18C39F2D3F%3Fref_%3Dast_bln">Smartish 手机</a>壳，因为它们的艺术设计，但我们特别喜欢适用于最新 iPhone 的<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1NtYXJ0aXNoLWlQaG9uZS1TbGltLUNhc2UtTGlnaHR3ZWlnaHQvZHAvQjBDN0hKS0pRNz90YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1iei0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYzI1YzA3NDctZjg3ZC00YzhmLWEzODItNGI3NmY5MWIyMjY1In0&amp;signature=AQAAAfsvdyeQptRigFDxfsOJ23dQ9xAwRNpmwQ04ZuB8oKEG&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSmartish-iPhone-Slim-Case-Lightweight%2Fdp%2FB0C7HJKJQ7" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/Smartish-iPhone-Slim-Case-Lightweight/dp/B0C7HJKJQ7?ref_=ast_sto_dp&amp;th=1">Gripmunk 系列</a>。从字面上看，这些薄型手机壳的边缘比 Spigen 的手机壳要粗糙一些 - Gripmunk 保护套具有纹理边缘，使它们更容易抓握并且不太可能从手中滑落，而手机壳的背面则展示了可爱的图案和设计，例如花卉阵列、宇宙场景等等。如果您想走真正的基本路线（没有羞耻），还有一些纯色选项，这些也都是 MagSafe 保护壳。如果你是一个极简主义者，不喜欢随身携带太多东西，你可以放弃你的钱包和弹簧，选择<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL1NtYXJ0aXNoLWlQaG9uZS0xNC1XYWxsZXQtQ2FzZS1DcmVkaXQtQ2FyZC1Ib2xkZXIvZHAvQjBDN0hLSllNQz90YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1iei0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYzI1YzA3NDctZjg3ZC00YzhmLWEzODItNGI3NmY5MWIyMjY1In0&amp;signature=AQAAAZmE5khGCIBRsw_Su8Be87SohVleF5AMfsrjmuehDnkN&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSmartish-iPhone-14-Wallet-Case-Credit-Card-Holder%2Fdp%2FB0C7HKJYMC" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/Smartish-iPhone-14-Wallet-Case-Credit-Card-Holder/dp/B0C7HKJYMC?ref_=ast_sto_dp">Smartish 的 Wallet Slayer</a> ，这是一款持卡包，边缘有类似的纹理，背面有一个套子。这款钱包盒最多可容纳三张信用卡和几张现金。</p><h2> Case-Mate Blox </h2><p><core-commerce id="5b931792bc994ffc9f4dd81143bd608a" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>如果您正在寻找一款大胆、引人注目、富有个性的保护套， <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAeYPt-bzJWJEYW1Xivkt1RdZknKCYGSnbcjcR_UeW3xm&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fstores%2FCase-Mate%2Fpage%2F68ACBEE5-0271-48BB-AF08-74EC76CFED4D%3Fref_%3Dast_bln">Case-Mate</a>有很多不错的选择可供考虑。它的 iPhone 15 系列拥有闪闪发光的保护壳、棱柱形保护套以及介于两者之间的一切，但最让我印象深刻的是<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0Nhc2UtTWF0ZS1CTE9YLWlQaG9uZS1Qcm8tQ2FzZS9kcC9CMENDM1hGM0RLP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWJ6LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJjMjVjMDc0Ny1mODdkLTRjOGYtYTM4Mi00Yjc2ZjkxYjIyNjUifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAXY1iyWegoiJJZ7lEhqrrDsR5uE9j7bF4OM3PVroLo_x&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FCase-Mate-BLOX-iPhone-Pro-Case%2Fdp%2FB0CC3XF3DK" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/Case-Mate-BLOX-iPhone-Pro-Case/dp/B0CC3XF3DK?ref_=ast_sto_dp&amp;th=1">Blox 系列</a>。这些保护壳具有方形边角，可为您的 iPhone 带来现代、块状的外观。将其与明亮的霓虹灯颜色相结合，您可能再也不用问朋友您的手机在哪里了 - 您不会错过它。我还很欣赏 ​​Blox 保护壳具有防指纹功能，可防止 10 英尺高处跌落，并具有内置磁性以兼容 MagSafe 配件。</p><h2>奥格尼奥雷</h2><p><core-commerce id="92dd9975c3c74f338daaff3cf994ac62" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>如果您想要一个环保的手机壳，现在您有比以前更多的选择。 <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL2luY2lwaW8uY29tL3BhZ2VzL29yZ2FuaWNvcmUiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImMyNWMwNzQ3LWY4N2QtNGM4Zi1hMzgyLTRiNzZmOTFiMjI2NSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAXwYdO_SLOmtjNvNeB3_jHL3Riwlk5md_e2F2MJ6hyTk&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fincipio.com%2Fpages%2Forganicore">Incipio 的 Organicore 系列</a>是我们的最爱之一，因为其高品质外壳 100% 可堆肥，提供良好的保护，而且最新型号还兼容 MagSafe。 They come in clear and opaque designs, and the latter has a buttery texture that makes the case feel more luxurious than you&#39;d think. Organicore cases will protect your iPhone from drops up to eight feet, and their raised edges will be the first line of defense your phone has against accidental dings and bumps. MagSafe accessories work fine, but we did find that the opaque case wasn&#39;t the grippiest out of the ones we tested. Best to stick to flat wireless chargers like <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDhMNU5QNk5HP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLWJ6LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJjMjVjMDc0Ny1mODdkLTRjOGYtYTM4Mi00Yjc2ZjkxYjIyNjUifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAeJLPwjZqL64ujjMdSJiRRxaTGMMuwbkwx3Sg0F7rxAb&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB08L5NP6NG">Apple&#39;s</a> , rather than vertical magnetic stands where gravity can take over.</p><h2> Cyrill Kajuk Mag </h2><p><core-commerce id="a797668447604b7f849f3054dc491824" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAUIhA1hHiZOseRiPBaoidSdGss3lRl84S5jHPOG7tVmh&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fstores%2FCYRILL%2Fpage%2F469D9AB2-5D23-4F33-AB0B-E6418ACC7A20%3Fref_%3Dast_bln">Cyrill</a> makes a number of sleek and elegant cases and the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL0NZUklMTC1Db21wYXRpYmxlLUxlYXRoZXItUHJvdGVjdGl2ZS1NaWNyb2ZpYmVyL2RwL0IwQzVaMjZQMk0_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tYnotMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImMyNWMwNzQ3LWY4N2QtNGM4Zi1hMzgyLTRiNzZmOTFiMjI2NSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAWiJpTzh7j1LY-qK9dzNeN7-xsVzZCniSaYji8RGTGun&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FCYRILL-Compatible-Leather-Protective-Microfiber%2Fdp%2FB0C5Z26P2M" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/CYRILL-Compatible-Leather-Protective-Microfiber/dp/B0C5Z26P2M?ref_=ast_sto_dp&amp;th=1">Kajuk Mag</a> is no exception. It&#39;s one of the thinnest and lightest cases we tried, but it does have four layers of protection: a soft microfiber lining, a sturdy PC back, TPU bumpers and a vegan leather exterior. Since the company doesn&#39;t boast a certain level of drop protection, this slim case is a good option for those that care more about aesthetics and case design, but also want a simple, protective layer standing between their iPhone and hard concrete. As the name suggests, you can use the Kajuk Mag with MagSafe accessories, and it even has an accessory hole built in, for those that want to attach charms, straps and other things.</p><h2> Peak Design Everyday Case </h2><p><core-commerce id="7f9cabb0a198413d80469ce5e206a66c" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Peak Design;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=8747aed1-6586-46eb-856d-c95a5318901b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Peak+Design&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAX5ifLUyfUt5JYRsrM2sAYxGfwrk4bb1Z_W1ibk9z5By&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.peakdesign.com%2Fproducts%2Feveryday-case%3Fvariant%3D39821980237901">Peak Design&#39;s Everyday Case</a> not only looks attractive, but it turns your phone into a bunch of different things when you pair it with any of the accessories in the company&#39;s mobile ecosystem. We like its protective rubberized bumper and nylon shell, and its SlimLink connector sits in the middle of the case&#39;s back, waiting for whichever gadgets you need that day. The company&#39;s mobile tripod is one of our favorites for taking better photos with your phone, but also propping it up any which way you need. Commuters can opt for the dashboard mount to keep their phone within reach while driving, or the bike mount when you need to read directions on its screen. If you use your phone for everything and want a case that can support all of that functionality, this one is a good option.</p><h2> Pelican Shield Kevlar </h2><p><core-commerce id="97cf9a44de194ede9a7f5d12852d20b8" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Maybe you work outdoors, go camping frequently or are simply a bit clumsier than most. Some of the best protection you can get for your iPhone comes from <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9QZWxpY2FuLVNoaWVsZC1LZXZsYXItQ29tcGF0aWJsZS1Qcm90ZWN0aW9uL2RwL0IwQjlOV0xOV0M_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tYnotMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImMyNWMwNzQ3LWY4N2QtNGM4Zi1hMzgyLTRiNzZmOTFiMjI2NSJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAczM1J6De6NqWb1MM5puJzJ6w7m8iKa_mw0ldWF_HAaa&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FPelican-Shield-Kevlar-Compatible-Protection%2Fdp%2FB0B9NWLNWC">Pelican&#39;s Shield Kevlar series cases</a> . Though they&#39;re a little pricey and admittedly bulky, that&#39;s how they safeguard your phone from up to 21-foot drops. The 5mm raised bumper provides shock-absorbing safety for the rear camera lens array as well as the handset as a whole, plus the secure edges and dustproof cover keep all unwanted debris out. Plus, these rugged cases are MagSafe compatible, so you don&#39;t have to sacrifice convenience when opting for as much protection as possible.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-iphone-cases-153035988.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-iphone-cases-153035988.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> c25c0747-f87d-4c8f-a382-4b76f91b2265</guid><dc:creator>瓦伦蒂娜·帕拉迪诺</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 15 Sep 2023 15:30:02 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694791803</ingested><modified> 2023-09-15T15:30:25+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Valentina Palladino]]></category><media:content height="960" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/fcabfdf0-51b3-11ee-bfbe-c7eb24fffb29" width="1280"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="960" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/fcabfdf0-51b3-11ee-bfbe-c7eb24fffb29" width="1280"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Cherlynn Low / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[An iPhone 15 Pro held in mid-air.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[iPhone 15 Pro ]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Spider-Man 2 is following the Sony sequel playbook, and I'm not mad about it]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Spider-Man is easily one of the most recognizable fictional characters of the last 50-plus years, appearing in countless iterations across comics, movies, cartoons, video games and other media I am surely forgetting. Fans will argue about the best iteration — but for my money, the Spider-universe Insomniac Games introduced in 2018 on the PS4 with <em>Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man</em> is an all-time great. It spent no time rehashing Peter Parker&#39;s origins, throwing the player into a vibrant and massive rendering of Manhattan. The city felt alive, with tons to do investigate and a horde of Spider-Man&#39;s most famous villains to contend with. It also skillfully introduced a world in which Parker would eventually fight side-by-side <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/miles-morales-ps5-review-spider-man-161228925.html">with a second Spider-Man, Miles Morales</a> .</p><p> But, most importantly, <em>Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man</em> was an absolute delight to play. Insomniac nailed the mechanics of swinging around the city and fighting bad guys to such a degree that I think web-slinging around Manhattan is up there with my all-time favorite game mechanics.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> As I&#39;ve contemplated with other single-player, story-drive masterpieces from Sony like <em>The Last of Us,</em> <em>Horizon Zero Dawn</em> and <em>God of War</em> : <a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:2;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-last-of-us-part-ii-review-070140792.html">What the hell</a> <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/horizon-forbidden-west-review-water-robot-dinos-080126554.html">do you do</a> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/god-of-war-ragnarok-review-ps5-162534113.html">for an encore</a> ? I played about two hours of <em>Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man 2</em> at a press event earlier this week, and it seems the answer is “go bigger.” That&#39;s the same tactic used for the sequels to those three games I mentioned earlier, and the results were always impressive, if not a bit overstuffed. Of course, it&#39;s too early to say whether Insomniac got the balance right, because we&#39;ve seen plenty of open-world games that simply try and do too much. But based on Insomniac&#39;s history and the excellent ingredients it has to work with, I have high hopes for the latest spider-adventure. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/021f88d0-53d3-11ee-ae27-c854b361d145" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/021f88d0-53d3-11ee-ae27-c854b361d145" style="height:2160px;width:3840px;" alt="Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man 2 - Harlem art" data-uuid="1d4cba6e-8d59-37e4-8408-cefdd369e265"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Insomniac Games</div></figure><p> My demo started well into the game&#39;s narrative — which I won&#39;t spend too much time on, as I didn&#39;t get the whole picture of what was going on. I do know that classic villain Kraven is hunting another iconic Spider-Man bad guy, Dr. Curt Conners (better known as the Lizard), and Peter and Miles are both trying to defend the city from Kraven&#39;s hunters while also finding a cure to turn the Lizard back into his mild-mannered human form.</p><p> In a demo like this, getting a feel for the gameplay is a lot more important than digging into story beats, and <em>Spider-Man 2</em> had plenty to show me. Because the world in this game is almost twice as big as the original, with the addition of Brooklyn and Queens, finding new ways for players to get around was a major focus for Insomniac. Enter the web wings, a tool that allows you to glide around the city, catching wind tunnels and updrafts that sling you around at high speed. It&#39;s not meant to replace the core web-slinging mechanic, but augment it. Given how amazing swinging around Manhattan felt in the original games (and still feels here), that&#39;s a tall order. But it didn&#39;t take me long to get the hang of gliding through long stretches of the city, and mixing in web-swings to regain height. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/957626d0-53d2-11ee-b9c6-e42f82f51b92" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/957626d0-53d2-11ee-b9c6-e42f82f51b92" style="height:2160px;width:3840px;" alt="Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man 2 - web wings" data-uuid="e2d37000-657e-30aa-ab01-d4158faa1eba"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Insomniac Games</div></figure><p> The web wings are also particularly useful in places like Central Park or Queens, where there aren&#39;t nearly as many tall buildings to swing from. Getting around Central Park always felt a little awkward in the first game, so this is a welcome addition that makes traversing different terrain much easier. It&#39;s also great for getting across rivers — or doing battle on them. Gameplay footage revealed earlier this year showed both Spider-Men chasing the Lizard down a river while also being chased by Kraven&#39;s hunters (both on the river and in the sky), and the web wings were crucial for catching up and dispatching the massive crew of baddies.</p><p> Another side mission saw me controlling Miles as he chased down one of Kraven&#39;s drones — to keep up with it, you had to use the web wings to draft behind it while downloading data from it. Once you got all the data downloaded, you could take it down, but getting all that data takes a while. So you need to stay right on its tail, twisting and turning throughout the city. There&#39;s definitely a learning curve to making tight turns and quick ascensions with the web wings, and I bounced off numerous buildings that slowed me down enough that the drone made its escape.</p><p> I got the hang of it after a few tries, but even then I was on the edge of my seat trying to keep pace – it almost had the feeling of a racing game. Challenges like this are a smart way of introducing these new mechanics and schooling players on how to best use them, though.</p><p> Unsurprisingly, combat has also gotten a few tweaks, though anyone who played the previous Insomniac games can jump right in here and start beating up the countless goons roaming New York City. Both Parker and Morales have four special moves that correspond to the four face buttons on the controller – holding L1 and pressing one of those buttons activates a special attack. When I was playing as Peter, they all involved the symbiote suit going wild, while Miles had variations on the electrical attacks introduced in his game. They charge up as you fight, and you have to wait for them to replenish; I assume you can also learn and slot new ones as the game progresses. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/6ee3e250-53d2-11ee-af9f-07a7ba5fe155" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/6ee3e250-53d2-11ee-af9f-07a7ba5fe155" style="height:2160px;width:3840px;" alt="Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man 2 - special attacks" data-uuid="08e27556-7b39-346c-b510-42b447f5f9eb"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Insomniac Games</div></figure><p> In the first games, mashing the circle button to dodge was a big part of combat, but Insomniac mixed things up here. Now, there are some enemies whose attacks you have to parry by pressing the block button at just the right moment – dodging won&#39;t keep you safe. Other attacks require a dodge, as they can break through any parry or block you try. These different attacks are represented by a color flash above the enemy, indicating when it&#39;s the right time to throw up a block or dodge away. Dealing with these attacks threw a wrench into the familiar gameplay, as it took me a while to remember that my old habits from prior games weren&#39;t going to be enough to keep me alive here.</p><p> The gadgets both Spider-Men carry got a big improvement over the older games, too. Before, you could hold down R1 and switch from your standard web-shooters to various other hardware to help you in battle. But now, R1 defaults to web-shooters, always, a change I appreciated. From there, you can hold R1 and select a face button to activate a specific gadget.</p><p> This gives you immediate access to as many as four gadgets at once, plus your web shooter. Truth be told, I didn&#39;t dive into the menus to find out much about the tools at my disposal, but they&#39;re things like web bombs that wrap up multiple enemies or shock traps that zap everyone around you. Naturally, all these abilities can be leveled up with skill points you accumulate through the game, and there are the expected skill trees here as well.</p><p> It&#39;s going to take more than just a few hours of playing to see just how well these new additions fit into the core game, but one thing was undeniable from the start: <em>Spider-Man 2</em> is a visual feast. It&#39;s the first game of the series developed exclusively for the PS5, and it shows in everything from the sunsets and water on the river to the details of the different spider-suits I tried on. Character models also look impressive, perhaps none more so than the Lizard himself, with glistening fangs and incredibly textured green skin. The amount of detail in that model was stunning, but Peter&#39;s symbiote suit is a close second. When it gets hurt, it writhes in pain and truly feels like a living creature. Even when it&#39;s just serving as a Spider-Man suit, the variety of textures and details is impressive – it&#39;s a lot more than just a black outfit. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/33dd1af0-53d2-11ee-bffd-66df39d2fd8f" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/33dd1af0-53d2-11ee-bffd-66df39d2fd8f" style="height:2160px;width:3840px;" alt="Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man 2 - symbiote suit" data-uuid="3c3b72d0-69fa-3d31-9988-ba7f6944e188"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Insomniac Games</div></figure><p> Perhaps the most exciting thing about this sequel, though, is the fact that you can control both Peter Parker and Miles Morales. When you&#39;re in the open world and not directly in a main story quest, you can swap between the two Spider-Men at will by going to your communicator and holding down a button, <em>GTA V</em> style. Each character has their own main quests, and the game will move you back and forth between the two depending on what&#39;s next on the docket, but there&#39;s plenty of freedom to pick your character and explore NYC.</p><p> There are also parts of the story that&#39;ll bounce you between both characters as things progress. We saw a look at this in the aforementioned <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/first-look-at-spider-man-2-gameplay-shows-spidey-in-the-venom-suit-212740681.html">gameplay preview</a> a few months ago, but I got to play it out this time. The battle started with me playing as Peter, beating up some thugs in a Queens neighborhood, but then it switches to Miles across the city so you can get the jump on more hunters before they track the Lizard down. Peter eventually joins you, all hell breaks loose, and then you&#39;re flying down the river taking out hunters on jet skis as Miles and bringing down a massive chopper as Peter.</p><p> All these changes were fluid and natural (but also very scripted) and the basic experience of controlling both Spiders-Man is similar enough that it didn&#39;t throw me off. I am hoping that there are missions where you can decide which character you want to use, or flip between both depending on what play style you&#39;re feeling at the moment. Regardless, having missions where you play as both significantly expanded the scope of this epic set piece. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/4b21adc0-53d2-11ee-b27a-3d0d5c25500d" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/4b21adc0-53d2-11ee-b27a-3d0d5c25500d" style="height:2160px;width:3840px;" alt="Marvel&#39;s Spider-Man 2 - the Lizard" data-uuid="13dbd698-cd96-3e2e-a214-87e5fb5546d0"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Insomniac Games</div></figure><p> The preview ended with Peter uncharacteristically going off on his own to track the Lizard down after he escapes into the sewers — he&#39;s clearly showing some symbiote-inspired darkness that Miles says is totally out of character for him. But the demo didn&#39;t stop, and I instead was treated to the only true “boss battle” of the demo, with Peter squaring off against Conners. This was a positively huge, multi-stage showdown that required me to use all the skills I picked up over the prior two hours, including a lot of well-timed dodging and all the special attacks I had at my disposal.</p><p> As with the big battles in prior Spider-Man games, there were multiple tricks I needed to figure out to make the Lizard vulnerable – just trying my standard set of attacks wasn&#39;t going to be enough. I died a handful of times trying to get the hang of it, but fortunately these deaths didn&#39;t feel cheap. Usually, it was a case of me not recognizing the need to dodge rather than block, or some other variation on me not executing a skill the game had taught me. Once I got the hang of things, I made semi-quick work of the Lizard. At least, I thought I did, until the demo ended on a big old cliffhanger that made me think Peter might pay a bit of a price for going rogue.</p><p> Fortunately, I won&#39;t have to wait long to find out how things turn out – <em>Spider-Man 2</em> will be out on the PS5 on October 20. We&#39;ll have to wait to do a full review before we can give it a full recommendation, but I think anyone who enjoyed the first games will want to check this one out. And if you haven&#39;t tried them before, you should be able to jump right into this new one without much trouble. While I enjoy the stories Insomniac has crafted for the two Spider-Men, the delight of swinging and fighting around NYC is still one of my favorite gaming experiences out there, and it&#39;s one that doesn&#39;t require an encyclopedic knowledge of Spider-Man&#39;s history.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/spider-man-2-following-sony-150058057.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/spider-man-2-following-sony-150058057.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> a52fc641-a7d2-440d-85d3-10993fe2ef0d</guid><dc:creator> Nathan Ingraham</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 15 Sep 2023 15:00:58 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1694790226</ingested><modified> 2023-09-15T15:03:56+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Nathan Ingraham]]></category><media:content height="2160" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/e079cba0-53d2-11ee-bff3-63f76552f8da" width="3840"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2160" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-09/e079cba0-53d2-11ee-bff3-63f76552f8da" width="3840"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Insomniac Games]]></medi